# 🏛️ Bidora — Live Auction Marketplace: Complete System Architecture

> **Status:** Architecture Planning & Implementation Document · **Version:** 1.1 · **Date:** 2026-03-01
>
> **Current Stack:** Next.js (Frontend) · Node.js + Express + TypeScript (Backend) · Prisma ORM · PostgreSQL (prod ready) · Socket.IO · Stripe (Payments) · Gemini/AI (Listing Assist)


---

> [!NOTE]
> This document is based on deep analysis of the **existing Bidora codebase**. You already have a solid foundation: [AuctionService](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/services/auctionService.ts#10-119), [EscrowService](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/services/escrowService.ts#4-187), [FraudService](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/services/fraudService.ts#6-52), `WebSocketService`, a cron engine, and a Prisma schema covering Users, Auctions, Bids, Escrow, Wallet, Shipping, Ratings, and Disputes. This plan **extends and formalizes** what exists rather than starting over.

---

## STEP 1 — System Decomposition

### Overview: The 11 Core Modules

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Auth & User System] --> B[Auction Engine]
    B --> C[Real-time Bidding System]
    C --> D[Escrow & Payment System]
    D --> E[Wallet System]
    B --> F[Shipping Module]
    A --> G[Rating & Trust System]
    C --> H[Fraud Detection Layer]
    D --> I[Notification System]
    B --> J[Admin Dashboard]
    H --> K[AI Features Layer]
    G --> K
```

---

### Module 1: Authentication & User System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Verify identity, manage sessions, enforce role-based access, handle KYC/verification tiers |
| **Inputs** | Email, password, phone, optional KYC documents |
| **Outputs** | JWT access token, refresh token, user profile object |
| **Depends On** | Nothing (base layer) |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `users` — core entity
- `refresh_tokens` — token rotation table *(missing, needs to be added)*
- `kyc_verifications` — document verification records *(missing)*
- `user_sessions` — device tracking for fraud *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Token theft / replay attacks → mitigate with token rotation + short TTL
- Brute force on login → rate limiting (already in [rateLimiter.ts](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/middlewares/rateLimiter.ts)) ✅
- SQLite has no `ENUM` type → your current schema uses `String` with manual validation; PostgreSQL migration will add proper enums

---

### Module 2: Auction Engine

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Create, schedule, manage, and finalize auctions; own the state machine |
| **Inputs** | Seller info, item data, pricing, start/end time, images |
| **Outputs** | Auction record, state change events, winner declaration |
| **Depends On** | Auth, Escrow Service, Fraud Service |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `auctions` ✅ (exists)
- `categories` ✅ (exists)
- `auction_images` — dedicated table for CDN image URLs *(currently a JSON string in SQLite)*
- `auction_views` — analytics table for view counts *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Cron job missing an expired auction window → your current 30-second poll is acceptable for MVP; in production, use BullMQ delayed jobs for precision
- Race condition on finalization → your `prisma.$transaction` wrapper mitigates this ✅
- Reserve price not met but escrow was initialized → your [finalizeAuction](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/services/auctionService.ts#71-118) handles the `reserveMet` check correctly ✅

---

### Module 3: Real-time Bidding System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Handle live bid events with sub-second latency, anti-snipe logic, and room-based broadcasting |
| **Inputs** | WebSocket message: `{ auctionId, amount }` + JWT auth token |
| **Outputs** | `new_bid` broadcast, `time_extended` broadcast, `bid_error` to requester |
| **Depends On** | Auth, Auction Engine, Fraud Service |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `bids` ✅ (exists)

**Failure Points:**
- Concurrent bids from multiple clients → `prisma.$transaction` provides serializable isolation ✅
- WebSocket connection loss mid-bid → client must receive an `ack` before assuming bid succeeded
- Single Socket.IO server is a bottleneck at scale → requires Redis Adapter for multi-node support *(not yet implemented)*

---

### Module 4: Escrow & Payment System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Hold buyer funds in trust from auction end until confirmed delivery; manage commission; handle disputes and refunds |
| **Inputs** | Auction winner + amount from Auction Engine |
| **Outputs** | `HELD` → `RELEASED`/`REFUNDED`/`DISPUTED` escrow state; wallet credit/debit events |
| **Depends On** | Auction Engine, Wallet System |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `escrow_payments` ✅ (exists)
- `payment_gateway_logs` — external payment processor webhooks *(missing; needed when integrating Razorpay/Stripe)*

**Failure Points:**
- Double-initialization of escrow for same auction → `@unique` constraint on `auctionId` in `EscrowPayment` prevents this ✅
- Auto-release race condition when dispute is raised simultaneously → `DISPUTED` status freeze must be atomic with dispute creation ✅

---

### Module 5: Wallet System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Manage user's internal wallet balance; track all money movement as immutable ledger entries |
| **Inputs** | Deposit request, withdrawal request, escrow events, commission deductions |
| **Outputs** | Updated balance, transaction history |
| **Depends On** | Auth, Escrow |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `wallet_transactions` ✅ (exists)
- `wallet_withdrawals` — separate table for withdrawal requests + bank details *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Balance going negative due to race on concurrent bids → `pendingFunds` field partially handles this; needs atomic `SELECT FOR UPDATE`
- User withdrawing while escrow is being processed → withdrawal must check `pendingFunds` ✅ (partially implemented)

---

### Module 6: Shipping Module

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Track physical delivery of auctioned items; trigger escrow release on delivery confirmation |
| **Inputs** | Seller provides courier + tracking number; optional webhook from courier API |
| **Outputs** | Shipping status updates, triggers escrow release on `DELIVERED` |
| **Depends On** | Auction Engine, Escrow |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `shipping_details` ✅ (exists)
- `shipping_address` — buyer's delivery address *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Seller marks shipped but never actually ships → buyer can open dispute
- Courier API not integrated → auto-release relies on buyer confirmation or 14-day timeout

---

### Module 7: Rating & Trust System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Build platform trust through post-transaction ratings; influence `trustScore` which gates bidding eligibility |
| **Inputs** | Completed auction, reviewer userId, score (1-5), comment |
| **Outputs** | Updated `trustScore` on User, public rating record |
| **Depends On** | Auction Engine (must be `COMPLETED` to rate) |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `ratings` ✅ (exists)

**Failure Points:**
- Rating manipulation — users creating fake accounts to boost scores → Fraud module must detect correlated rating patterns
- Rating a user without completing a transaction → must gate on `COMPLETED` status

---

### Module 8: Fraud Detection Layer

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Protect platform integrity by detecting bid manipulation, account farming, shill bidding, and abnormal patterns |
| **Inputs** | Bid events, user session data, IP/device info, rating events |
| **Outputs** | `suspiciousFlags` increments, bid blocking, user suspension signals |
| **Depends On** | Auth, Bidding System, Rating System |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `fraud_events` — structured log of all suspicious activity *(missing)*
- `ip_logs` — IP + device fingerprint per session *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Over-blocking legitimate power users → flag system needs calibrated thresholds + human review queue
- False negatives on sophisticated fraud → rule-based is baseline; AI layer augments it

---

### Module 9: Notification System

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Deliver real-time and async notifications for bids, wins, payments, disputes, and shipping |
| **Inputs** | System events from all modules |
| **Outputs** | In-app notifications (WebSocket), push notifications, email, SMS |
| **Depends On** | Auth, ALL other modules (subscriber) |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `notifications` — persistent notification records *(missing)*
- `notification_preferences` — user-level opt-in settings *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Notification storm on high-bid auctions → debounce + batching for non-critical events
- Email/SMS failure → must have retry queue (BullMQ or SQS)

---

### Module 10: Admin Dashboard

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Provide platform operators with visibility and control over auctions, users, disputes, financials, and fraud alerts |
| **Inputs** | Admin JWT (role = `ADMIN`), dispute IDs, user IDs, auction IDs |
| **Outputs** | Reports, dispute resolutions, user bans, manual auction overrides |
| **Depends On** | ALL modules |

**Database Tables Required:**
- `admin_action_logs` — audit trail of all admin operations *(missing)*

**Failure Points:**
- Unauthorized access → strict `ADMIN` role check middleware (your [authMiddleware.ts](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.ts) covers this structure)
- Admin resolving dispute incorrectly → all decisions must be logged with `adminNotes` ✅

---

### Module 11: AI Features Layer

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Purpose** | Augment rule-based systems with ML-powered fraud detection, price suggestions, and personalized recommendations |
| **Inputs** | Historical bid patterns, user behavior, item descriptions |
| **Outputs** | Fraud risk scores, recommended starting prices, personalized auction feeds |
| **Depends On** | ALL modules (read-only consumer) |

**Failure Points:**
- Model drift over time → requires retraining pipeline
- Over-spending on inference → use lightweight models or rule+ML hybrid

---

## STEP 2 — Database Architecture Planning

> **Migration Path:** Your current schema uses SQLite for development. The design below targets **PostgreSQL** for production. Key differences: proper `ENUM` types, `ARRAY` columns, `TEXT[]`, `JSONB`, full-text search, `SELECT FOR UPDATE`, and advisory locks.

---

### Critical Tables Schema

#### `users`
```sql
CREATE TYPE user_role AS ENUM ('BUYER', 'SELLER', 'ADMIN');
CREATE TYPE verified_status AS ENUM ('BASIC', 'VERIFIED', 'PREMIUM');

CREATE TABLE users (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    email           TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    phone           TEXT UNIQUE,
    password_hash   TEXT NOT NULL,
    role            user_role NOT NULL DEFAULT 'BUYER',
    verified_status verified_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'BASIC',
    full_name       TEXT,
    avatar_url      TEXT,
    wallet_balance  DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.00,
    pending_funds   DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.00,
    trust_score     DECIMAL(3,1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 5.0,
    suspicious_flags INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    is_suspended    BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    last_login_at   TIMESTAMPTZ,
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes
CREATE INDEX idx_users_email ON users(email);
CREATE INDEX idx_users_role ON users(role);
CREATE INDEX idx_users_trust_score ON users(trust_score);
CREATE INDEX idx_users_suspended ON users(is_suspended) WHERE is_suspended = TRUE;
```

**Relationships:** 1-to-many with `auctions`, `bids`, `wallet_transactions`, `ratings`, `escrow_payments`

---

#### `refresh_tokens` *(NEW — missing from codebase)*
```sql
CREATE TABLE refresh_tokens (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    token_hash  TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    device_info TEXT,
    ip_address  INET,
    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    revoked     BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_refresh_tokens_user ON refresh_tokens(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_refresh_tokens_token ON refresh_tokens(token_hash);
```

---

#### `auctions`
```sql
CREATE TYPE auction_status AS ENUM (
    'DRAFT', 'SCHEDULED', 'LIVE', 'ENDED',
    'PAYMENT_PENDING', 'PAID', 'SHIPPED', 'DELIVERED',
    'COMPLETED', 'DISPUTED', 'CANCELLED'
);

CREATE TABLE auctions (
    id                  UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    seller_id           UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    title               TEXT NOT NULL,
    description         TEXT NOT NULL,
    category_id         INT NOT NULL REFERENCES categories(id),
    image_urls          TEXT[] NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
    starting_price      DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,
    reserve_price       DECIMAL(12,2),
    current_highest_bid DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.00,
    bid_increment       DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 1.00,   -- min bid step
    start_time          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    end_time            TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    status              auction_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'DRAFT',
    commission_rate     DECIMAL(4,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 7.00,
    shipping_cost       DECIMAL(8,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.00,
    view_count          INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    bid_count           INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes (Critical for performance)
CREATE INDEX idx_auctions_status ON auctions(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_auctions_end_time ON auctions(end_time);
CREATE INDEX idx_auctions_seller ON auctions(seller_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_auctions_category ON auctions(category_id);
-- Compound: powers the "Find live auctions ending soon" query
CREATE INDEX idx_auctions_live_end ON auctions(status, end_time) WHERE status = 'LIVE';
```

**Relationships:** Many-to-1 with `users` (seller), 1-to-many with `bids`, 1-to-1 with `escrow_payments`, `shipping_details`

---

#### `bids`
```sql
CREATE TABLE bids (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auction_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    bidder_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    amount      DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,
    is_winning  BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    is_auto_bid BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Critical indexes for bidding engine
CREATE INDEX idx_bids_auction ON bids(auction_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_bids_bidder ON bids(bidder_id);
-- Powers "get highest bid" validation
CREATE INDEX idx_bids_auction_amount ON bids(auction_id, amount DESC);
-- Powers "get winning bid" lookup
CREATE INDEX idx_bids_winning ON bids(auction_id) WHERE is_winning = TRUE;
```

**Relationships:** Many-to-1 with `auctions`, Many-to-1 with `users`

---

#### `auto_bids` *(NEW — Auto-bidding feature)*
```sql
CREATE TABLE auto_bids (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auction_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    bidder_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    max_amount  DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,
    is_active   BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(auction_id, bidder_id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_auto_bids_auction ON auto_bids(auction_id) WHERE is_active = TRUE;
```

---

#### `escrow_payments`
```sql
CREATE TYPE escrow_status AS ENUM ('HELD', 'RELEASED', 'REFUNDED', 'DISPUTED', 'CANCELLED');

CREATE TABLE escrow_payments (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auction_id      UUID UNIQUE NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    buyer_id        UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    seller_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    amount          DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,
    platform_fee    DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,
    payout_amount   DECIMAL(12,2) GENERATED ALWAYS AS (amount - platform_fee) STORED,
    status          escrow_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'HELD',
    auto_release_at TIMESTAMPTZ,     -- 14 days after SHIPPED, if no dispute
    released_at     TIMESTAMPTZ,
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_escrow_status ON escrow_payments(status);
-- Powers the cron: "Find escrows eligible for auto-release"
CREATE INDEX idx_escrow_auto_release ON escrow_payments(auto_release_at)
    WHERE status = 'HELD' AND auto_release_at IS NOT NULL;
```

---

#### `wallet_transactions`
```sql
CREATE TYPE wallet_tx_type AS ENUM (
    'DEPOSIT', 'WITHDRAWAL', 'ESCROW_HELD', 'ESCROW_RELEASED',
    'COMMISSION', 'REFUND', 'ADJUSTMENT', 'PAYMENT'
);
CREATE TYPE wallet_tx_status AS ENUM ('PENDING', 'COMPLETED', 'FAILED', 'REVERSED');

CREATE TABLE wallet_transactions (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    amount      DECIMAL(12,2) NOT NULL,  -- positive = credit, negative = debit
    type        wallet_tx_type NOT NULL,
    status      wallet_tx_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'COMPLETED',
    reference_id UUID,       -- links to escrow_id, dispute_id, etc.
    description TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_wallet_tx_user ON wallet_transactions(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_wallet_tx_type ON wallet_transactions(type);
CREATE INDEX idx_wallet_tx_created ON wallet_transactions(created_at DESC);
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `wallet_transactions` is an **append-only ledger**. Never UPDATE or DELETE rows. Balance is always derived by summing all transactions for a user.

---

#### `shipping_details`
```sql
CREATE TYPE shipping_status AS ENUM ('PENDING', 'LABEL_CREATED', 'IN_TRANSIT', 'DELIVERED', 'RETURNED');

CREATE TABLE shipping_details (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auction_id      UUID UNIQUE NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    buyer_address_id UUID REFERENCES shipping_addresses(id),
    tracking_number TEXT,
    courier         TEXT,
    status          shipping_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PENDING',
    shipped_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,
    delivered_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

---

#### `shipping_addresses` *(NEW)*
```sql
CREATE TABLE shipping_addresses (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    full_name   TEXT NOT NULL,
    line1       TEXT NOT NULL,
    line2       TEXT,
    city        TEXT NOT NULL,
    state       TEXT NOT NULL,
    pincode     TEXT NOT NULL,
    country     TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'IN',
    phone       TEXT,
    is_default  BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_shipping_addr_user ON shipping_addresses(user_id);
```

---

#### `ratings`
```sql
CREATE TABLE ratings (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    from_user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    to_user_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    auction_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    score       SMALLINT NOT NULL CHECK (score BETWEEN 1 AND 5),
    comment     TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(from_user_id, auction_id)    -- one rating per transaction
);

CREATE INDEX idx_ratings_to_user ON ratings(to_user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_ratings_auction ON ratings(auction_id);
```

---

#### `disputes`
```sql
CREATE TYPE dispute_status AS ENUM (
    'OPEN', 'UNDER_REVIEW', 'RESOLVED_REFUND_BUYER',
    'RESOLVED_RELEASE_SELLER', 'CLOSED'
);

CREATE TABLE disputes (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auction_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auctions(id),
    buyer_id    UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    reason      TEXT NOT NULL,
    evidence_urls TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    status      dispute_status NOT NULL DEFAULT 'OPEN',
    admin_notes TEXT,
    resolved_by UUID REFERENCES users(id),
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_disputes_status ON disputes(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_disputes_auction ON disputes(auction_id);
```

---

#### `fraud_events` *(NEW)*
```sql
CREATE TYPE fraud_event_type AS ENUM (
    'RAPID_BIDDING', 'LOW_BALANCE_BID', 'MULTIPLE_ACCOUNTS',
    'SHILL_BID_PATTERN', 'SUSPICIOUS_RATING', 'IP_ANOMALY'
);

CREATE TABLE fraud_events (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    event_type  fraud_event_type NOT NULL,
    auction_id  UUID REFERENCES auctions(id),
    metadata    JSONB,           -- flexible: { ipAddress, bidAmount, patternScore }
    risk_score  DECIMAL(4,2),
    resolved    BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_fraud_events_user ON fraud_events(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_fraud_events_type ON fraud_events(event_type);
CREATE INDEX idx_fraud_events_unresolved ON fraud_events(resolved) WHERE resolved = FALSE;
```

---

#### `notifications` *(NEW)*
```sql
CREATE TYPE notification_type AS ENUM (
    'BID_PLACED', 'OUTBID', 'AUCTION_WON', 'AUCTION_ENDED',
    'PAYMENT_REQUIRED', 'PAYMENT_RECEIVED', 'ITEM_SHIPPED',
    'ITEM_DELIVERED', 'DISPUTE_OPENED', 'DISPUTE_RESOLVED', 'SYSTEM'
);

CREATE TABLE notifications (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    type        notification_type NOT NULL,
    title       TEXT NOT NULL,
    body        TEXT NOT NULL,
    reference_id UUID,           -- auction_id, dispute_id, etc.
    is_read     BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_user_unread ON notifications(user_id, is_read)
    WHERE is_read = FALSE;
CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_user_created ON notifications(user_id, created_at DESC);
```

---

### Scaling & Caching Strategy

| Layer | What to Cache in Redis | TTL |
|-------|----------------------|-----|
| Live Auction State | `auction:{id}:currentBid`, `auction:{id}:endTime`, `auction:{id}:bidCount` | Until auction ends |
| Active Bidders Count | `auction:{id}:watchers` | 60s |
| User Session | JWT validation result | 5 min |
| User Balance Eligibility | `user:{id}:canBid` flag | 30s |
| Category List | Full category tree | 1 hour |
| Leaderboard/Feed | Top 10 active auctions | 30s |

**Critical for Scaling:**
1. `auctions(status, end_time)` compound index → powers the live feed
2. `bids(auction_id, amount DESC)` → powers bid validation
3. `wallet_transactions(user_id)` → heavy read; balance must be cached
4. `notifications(user_id, is_read=FALSE)` → partial index prevents full-table scans

---

## STEP 3 — Auction State Machine Design

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> DRAFT : Seller creates listing
    DRAFT --> SCHEDULED : Seller publishes + sets future start time
    DRAFT --> CANCELLED : Seller cancels before publishing
    SCHEDULED --> LIVE : Cron/Timer triggers at startTime
    SCHEDULED --> CANCELLED : Seller cancels before going live
    LIVE --> ENDED : No bids placed when endTime reached
    LIVE --> PAYMENT_PENDING : Winning bid exists & reserve met at endTime
    LIVE --> DISPUTED : Admin/system intervention
    PAYMENT_PENDING --> PAID : Buyer completes payment (wallet deduction + escrow init)
    PAYMENT_PENDING --> CANCELLED : Payment timeout (48h) exceeded
    PAID --> SHIPPED : Seller provides tracking number
    SHIPPED --> DELIVERED : Buyer confirms delivery OR auto-release after 14 days
    SHIPPED --> DISPUTED : Buyer opens dispute before delivery confirmed
    DELIVERED --> COMPLETED : Escrow auto-released, ratings unlocked
    DELIVERED --> DISPUTED : Buyer disputes within 48h of delivery confirmation
    DISPUTED --> COMPLETED : Admin resolves → RELEASE_SELLER
    DISPUTED --> ENDED : Admin resolves → REFUND_BUYER
    COMPLETED --> [*]
    CANCELLED --> [*]
    ENDED --> [*]
```

### State Transition Rules

| From → To | Trigger | Who Can Trigger | Automation |
|-----------|---------|-----------------|------------|
| `DRAFT → SCHEDULED` | Seller publishes listing | Seller | Manual |
| `SCHEDULED → LIVE` | `startTime` reached | **Cron Job** | ✅ Automated every 30s |
| `LIVE → PAYMENT_PENDING` | `endTime` reached + bids exist + reserve met | **Cron Job** | ✅ Automated every 30s |
| `LIVE → ENDED` | `endTime` reached + no valid bids | **Cron Job** | ✅ Automated |
| `PAYMENT_PENDING → PAID` | Buyer pays via wallet | Buyer | Manual + 48h timeout |
| `PAYMENT_PENDING → CANCELLED` | 48h payment timeout | **Cron Job** | ✅ Automated |
| `PAID → SHIPPED` | Seller submits tracking | Seller | Manual |
| `SHIPPED → DELIVERED` | Buyer confirms OR 14-day auto-release | Buyer / **Cron Job** | Hybrid |
| `DELIVERED → COMPLETED` | Escrow released | **System** | ✅ Automated |
| `ANY → DISPUTED` | Buyer raises dispute | Buyer | Manual |
| `DISPUTED → COMPLETED` | Admin resolves → Seller | Admin | Manual |
| `DISPUTED → ENDED` | Admin resolves → Buyer refund | Admin | Manual |

### Error Handling Logic

- **Double transition prevention:** All state changes use `prisma.$transaction` with a `WHERE status = 'EXPECTED_STATUS'` guard. If the row has already transitioned, the update affects 0 rows and the transaction rolls back.
- **Cron idempotency:** [finalizeAuction](file:///c:/Users/PRUTHVIRAJ/Desktop/Bidora/backend/src/services/auctionService.ts#71-118) checks `status !== 'LIVE'` at the start — safe to call multiple times.
- **Payment timeout:** A separate cron (every 1 hour) scans for `PAYMENT_PENDING` auctions older than 48h and cancels them + refunds if escrow was partially initialized.

