## STEP 6 — Fraud & Risk System

### System Architecture

```
All Events (Bids, Logins, Ratings, Payouts)
    │
    ▼
[Event Capture Layer] ─── Logs every action with metadata:
                           { userId, ipAddress, deviceFingerprint, timestamp, action }
    │
    ▼
[Rule Engine] ─── Fast heuristics (fired synchronously on bid path):
    ├── suspiciousFlags >= 5 → BLOCK
    ├── trustScore < 2.0 → BLOCK
    ├── bidAmount > 10x historical average → FLAG
    ├── Same IP bidding against self (shill) → FLAG
    └── > 10 bids in 60 seconds → RATE LIMIT
    │
    ▼
[Pattern Analyzer] ─── Async analysis (fired post-event via BullMQ):
    ├── Bid clustering (many bids just under winning bid)
    ├── New account + high-value bid within 24h of registration
    ├── Multiple accounts sharing same device fingerprint
    └── Rating manipulation (account X always rates account Y 5 stars)
    │
    ▼
[Risk Scorer] ─── Aggregates rule hits → assigns risk_score (0.0–1.0)
    │
    ├── risk_score > 0.7 → Auto-suspend + notify admin
    ├── risk_score 0.4–0.7 → Flag + add to review queue
    └── risk_score < 0.4 → Log only
```

### Specific Fraud Vectors & Mitigations

| Threat | Detection | Mitigation |
|--------|-----------|------------|
| **Shill bidding** | Seller's IP or device matches bidder | Block + flag both accounts |
| **Bid manipulation** | Bid pattern: many small bids escalating with no intention to pay | Suspend + escrow forfeiture |
| **Fake accounts** | Same device fingerprint, email pattern, IP block | Merge/ban accounts |
| **Payment ghosting** | Win auction, never pay | 3-strike rule → permanent ban; listing fee forfeiture |
| **Feedback bombing** | Mass negative ratings from coordinated accounts | Rate-limit ratings; require completed transaction |
| **Rapid outlier bids** | Bid > 5x current highest bid | Require extra confirmation step |

### Where AI Assists Fraud Detection
- **Anomaly detection:** ML model scores bid patterns against baseline; flags deviations > 2σ
- **Device fingerprint clustering:** ML groups devices that look similar despite different IPs
- **For MVP:** Rule-based is sufficient. Add ML in Phase 3.

