## STEP 7 — AI Feature Planning

### Honest Assessment: Where AI Adds Real Value vs. Where Rules Work Fine

| Feature | AI or Rules? | Reasoning |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| Bid increment validation | **Rules** | Simple math, deterministic |
| Anti-sniping timer | **Rules** | Deterministic time logic |
| Basic fraud flags | **Rules** | Threshold-based, explainable |
| Reserve price suggestion | **AI** ✅ | Requires market context |
| Anomaly detection in bids | **AI** ✅ | Pattern recognition at scale |
| Category auto-tagging | **AI** ✅ | NLP on item descriptions |
| Personalized auction feed | **AI** ✅ | Collaborative filtering |
| Price trend prediction | **AI** ✅ | Time-series ML |
| Dispute outcome prediction | **Rules + AI** | Hybrid for admin assist |

### Recommended First AI Feature: **Suggested Starting Price**

**Why?**
- Highest seller pain point: "_What price should I start my auction at?_"
- Low infrastructure cost: one ML model, called once per listing
- High value: directly impacts seller success rate and platform liquidity
- Feasible with small dataset: train on completed auction history

**Implementation Plan:**
```
Input:  { category, title_keywords, condition, image_embeddings }
Model:  Gradient Boosted Trees (XGBoost) — lightweight, interpretable
Output: suggested_starting_price ± confidence_range
Where:  Called from "Create Listing" flow; optional, not blocking
Cost:   Trivially low — one inference per listing, no real-time requirement
```

### AI Stack Recommendation
- **Model training:** Python + scikit-learn / XGBoost (separate microservice)
- **Serving:** FastAPI + model pickle (simple, cheap)
- **Integration:** REST call from Node backend to AI microservice
- **For MVP:** Skip AI entirely. Build it in Phase 4.

> [!WARNING]
> Do NOT integrate LLMs (GPT-4, Gemini) into the hot bid path. The latency (200-500ms) and cost are incompatible with real-time bidding requirements.

