## STEP 9 — Build Order Plan (Phased Implementation Roadmap)

### Phase 1 — Core Foundation (Weeks 1–4)
**Goal:** A working end-to-end auction with payment

| Module | Tasks |
|--------|-------|
| Auth | Refresh token table, email verification, role guards |
| Auction Engine | DRAFT → LIVE state machine, image upload to CDN |
| Bidding System | WebSocket bidding (already exists ✅), anti-snipe ✅, bid increment |
| Escrow | Basic HELD → RELEASED flow (already exists ✅) |
| Wallet | Deposit, escrow hold, payout (partially exists ✅) |
| Database | Migrate SQLite → PostgreSQL, add all missing tables |
| Frontend | Live auction screen, basic bid flow |

**Why first?** Without core auction + payment working, nothing else matters. Trust and money are the heart of the platform.

---

### Phase 2 — Trust & Usability (Weeks 5–8)
**Goal:** Users trust the platform; sellers and buyers feel safe

| Module | Tasks |
|--------|-------|
| Shipping | Shipping address CRUD, tracking number submission, delivery confirmation |
| Ratings | Post-auction rating flow, trust score recalculation |
| Notifications | In-app notifications via WebSocket, email notifications |
| Disputes | Buyer dispute flow, admin resolution UI |
| Admin Dashboard | Dispute queue, user management, auction oversight |
| UX Polish | Swipe-to-bid, quick increments, micro-animations |

**Why second?** Ratings and shipping are table stakes for marketplace trust. Without them, no repeat usage.

---

### Phase 3 — Fraud & Security Hardening (Weeks 9–12)
**Goal:** Platform integrity; prevent bad actors at scale

| Module | Tasks |
|--------|-------|
| Fraud Detection | `fraud_events` table, rule engine, rate limiting by IP |
| Device Fingerprinting | `ip_logs`, device tracking on login/bid |
| Auto-Bid System | `auto_bids` table, cascade logic |
| Redis Integration | Live bid state caching, session caching |
| Multi-node WebSocket | Redis Adapter for Socket.IO |

**Why third?** You need real users and real data before fraud patterns are meaningful. Build fraud detection with real signals.

---

### Phase 4 — AI & Personalization (Weeks 13–18)
**Goal:** Intelligent platform that grows with use

| Module | Tasks |
|--------|-------|
| AI Price Suggestions | Train on completed auction data; serve via FastAPI |
| AI Fraud Scoring | Upgrade rule engine with ML anomaly scores |
| Personalized Feed | Collaborative filtering on bid/view history |
| Category Auto-tagging | NLP on listing descriptions |

**Why fourth?** You need sufficient data volume (1000+ completed auctions) before ML adds reliable signal over rules.

---

### Phase 5 — Scale & UX Excellence (Weeks 19–24)
**Goal:** Handle 10x traffic; delight users

| Module | Tasks |
|--------|-------|
| BullMQ Job Queue | Replace cron with queued jobs for auction finalization |
| PgBouncer | Connection pooling for PostgreSQL |
| CDN & Image Optimization | Lazy loading, WebP conversion, image resizing |
| PWA | Offline support, push notifications |
| Analytics Dashboard | Seller analytics: views, bid velocity, conversion rate |
| A/B Testing | Test swipe-to-bid vs tap-to-bid conversion |

**Why fifth?** Premature optimization is the enemy of shipping. Optimize for the traffic you actually have, not imaginary traffic.

---

